ria In Mayor's Race |url=https://www.kpbs.org/news/2019/aug/21/todd-gloria-democratic-party-endorsement-mayor/ |publisher=KPBS |date=August 21, 2019 |accessdate=August 21, 2019}}</ref>\n*San Diego Chamber of Commerce<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lewis |first1=Scott |last2=Keatts |first2=Andrew |title=Politics Report: Holy Endorsement \u2014 Chamber Chooses Todd |url=https://www.voiceofsandiego.org/topics/politics/politics-report-holy-endorsement-chamber-chooses-todd/ |work=Voice of San Diego |date=November 23, 2019 |accessdate=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n*San Diego & Imperial Counties Labor Council, [[AFL-CIO]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Garrick |first1=David |title=Labor unions lining up behind Gloria in San Diego mayor's race |url=https://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/communities/san-diego/story/2019-11-05/labor-unions-lining-up-behind-gloria-in-san-diego-mayors-race |work=The San Diego Union-Tribune |date=November 5, 2019 |accessdate=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Equality California]]<ref>{{cite web |title=Equality California Endorses Todd Gloria's Historic Bid for San Diego Mayor |url=https://www.eqca.org/todd-gloria-2020-endorsement/ |website=Equality California |language=en |date=8 March 2019 |accessdate=April 27, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Gloria_endorse\" />\n*[[Laborers' International Union of North America]], Local 89<ref name=\"Mapp_4-9-19\" />\n*San Diego City Firefighters Association, [[International Association of Fire Fighters]] Local 145<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jennewein |first1=Chris |title=Firefighters Union Endorses Gloria for Mayor, Brennan for City Council |url=https://timesofsandiego.com/politics/2019/06/20/firefighters-union-endorses-gloria-for-mayor-brennan-for-city-council/ |work=Times of San Diego |date=June 20, 2019 |accessdate=June 21, 2019}}</ref>\n*San Diego Municipal Employees Association<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jennewein |first1=Chris |title=City Employees Union Endorses Todd Gloria for San Diego Mayor |url=https://timesofsandiego.com/politics/2019/07/18/cit-employees-union-endorses-todd-gloria-for-san-diego-mayor/ |work=Times of San Diego |date=July 18, 2019 |accessdate=July 18, 2019}}</ref>\n*San Diego Police Officers Association<ref>{{cite news |last1=Libby |first1=Sara |title=Morning Report: The Wild World of Water Vending |url=https://www.voiceofsandiego.org/topics/news/morning-report-the-wild-world-of-water-vending/ |work=Voice of San Diego |date=October 1, 2019 |accessdate=October 1, 2019}}</ref>\n*[[Service Employees International Union]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lewis |first1=Scott |last2=Keatts |first2=Andrew |title=Politics Report: Fletcher Staying Out of 53rd |url=https://www.voiceofsandiego.org/topics/politics/politics-report-fletcher-staying-out-of-53rd/ |work=Voice of San Diego |date=September 21, 2019 |accessdate=September 21, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Scott Sherman\n| list =\n;Officeholders\n*[[Kevin Faulconer]], [[Mayor of San Diego]]<ref name=\"UT_endorse\" />\n;Organizations\n*San Diego County [[Republican Party (US)|Republican Party]]<ref name=\"Stone_Sherman\">{{cite news |last1=Stone |first1=Ken |title=Common Sense Over Nonsense? Scott Sherman Explains Late Run for Mayor |url=https://timesofsandiego.com/politics/2020/02/05/common-sense-over-nonsense-scott-sherman-explains-late-run-for-mayor/ |accessdate=February 7, 2020 |work=Times of San Diego |date=February 6, 2020}}</ref>\n*Lincoln Club of San Diego County<ref name=\"Stone_Sherman\" />\n}}\n\n==Primary election==\nThe primary election was held on Tuesday, March 3, 2020. In the initial results, Gloria led with more than 40% of the vote and was projected to advance to the general election. Sherman narrowly led  Bry by a little over 3,000 votes for the second spot in the general election.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bowen |first1=Andrew |last2=Tragesar |first2=Claire |title=Gloria Headed For San Diego Mayor Runoff; Sherman, Bry Battling For Second Spot |url=https://www.kpbs.org/news/2020/mar/03/election-2020-san-diego-mayor-results/ |accessdate=March 5, 2020 |work=KPBS Public Media |issue=March 4, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> By the second day of counting, Bry had reduced Sherman's margin for the second spot by 30 percent to 2,140.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Garrick |first1=David |title=Sherman's lead over Bry shrinks in battle for second slot in mayoral runoff |url=https://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/communities/san-diego/story/2020-03-05/shermans-lead-over-bry-shrinks-in-battle-for-second-slot-in-mayoral-runoff |work=San Diego Union-Tribune |date=March 6, 2020}}</ref> Bry continued to gain on Sherman as more votes were counted, and on March 16 her votes surpassed his.<ref>{{cite news |author1=City News Service |title=Bry Passes Sherman In Mayoral Race With Razor-Thin Margin |url=https://www.kpbs.org/news/2020/mar/16/bry-passes-sherman-mayoral-race-razor-thin-margin/ |accessdate=March 16, 2020 |work=KPBS Public Media |date=March 16, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> The final results released in early April confirmed that Gloria would face Bry in the runoff. This guaranteed that a Democrat would be elected mayor of San Diego for only the third time since 1971.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Trageser |first1=Claire |title=It's Official: Next San Diego Mayor Will Be A Democrat |url=https://www.kpbs.org/news/2020/apr/03/its-official-next-san-diego-mayor-will-be-democrat/ |accessdate=April 8, 2020 |work=KPBS Public Media |date=April 3, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n===Polling===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:90%;text-align:center;\"\n|- valign= bottom\n! style=\"width:175px;\"| Poll source\n! style=\"width:125px;\"| Date(s)<br />administered\n! Sample<br />size\n! Margin<br />of error\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Barbara<br />Bry\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Todd<br />Gloria\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Rich<br />Riel\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Scott<br />Sherman\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Gita<br />Applebaum<br />Singh\n! style=\"width:60px;\"| Tasha<br />Williamson\n! Undecided\n|-\n| align=center | [http://ww