struction-de-notre-dame |website=[[Les Derni\u00e8res Nouvelles d'Alsace]] |accessdate=23 April 2019 |language=fr |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416113934/https://www.dna.fr/actualite/2019/04/16/les-promesses-de-dons-affluent-pour-la-reconstruction-de-notre-dame |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Martin Bouygues|Bouygues]] family (\u20ac10M)<ref>{{cite web |language=fr-FR |title=Entreprises et grandes fortunes se mobilisent pour la reconstruction de Notre-Dame |work=[[La Croix]] |date=16 April 2019 |issn=0242-6056 |url=https://www.la-croix.com/Economie/Entreprises-grandes-fortunes-mobilisent-reconstruction-Notre-Dame-2019-04-16-1301016005 |accessdate=16 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190416120223/https://www.la-croix.com/Economie/Entreprises-grandes-fortunes-mobilisent-reconstruction-Notre-Dame-2019-04-16-1301016005 |archive-date=16 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n* [[Marc Ladreit de Lacharri\u00e8re|De Lacharri\u00e8re]] family & [[FIMALAC]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"Cagnottelemonde2\" />\n* [[\u00cele-de-France]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"Cagnottelemonde2\" />\n* [[Soci\u00e9t\u00e9 G\u00e9n\u00e9rale]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"boursorama.com\">{{cite web |url=https://www.boursorama.com/actualites/le-secteur-prive-promet-autour-de-700-millions-d-euros-pour-reconstruire-notre-dame-2dd239e4d8c0d278d0c6425acf2a02bc |title=Le secteur priv\u00e9 promet autour de 700 millions d'euros pour reconstruire Notre-Dame |date=16 April 2019 |website=Boursorama |language=fr |agency=Agence France-Presse (AFP)}}</ref>\n* [[Groupe BPCE|BPCE]] (\u20ac10M)<ref name=\"boursorama.com\" />\n}}\n\nThere have been many additional pledges for smaller, or undisclosed, amounts.<ref name=\"anger\">{{cite news |last1=Petrequin |first1=Samuel |title=Anger followed Notre Dame grief for yellow vest protesters |url=https://apnews.com/efb3aba4f029493a9b730d0b532c01bb |work=AP News |date=19 April 2019 |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420031730/https://apnews.com/efb3aba4f029493a9b730d0b532c01bb |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a478180/Vlada-Srbije-uputila-Francuskoj-milion-evra-za-obnovu-katedrale-Notr-Dam.html |title=Vlada Srbije uputila Francuskoj milion evra za obnovu katedrale Notr Dam |website=N1 Srbija |language=sr-Latn |accessdate=22 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190422135412/http://rs.n1info.com/Vesti/a478180/Vlada-Srbije-uputila-Francuskoj-milion-evra-za-obnovu-katedrale-Notr-Dam.html |archive-date=22 April 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\nA proposal by former minister [[Jean-Jacques Aillagon]] that corporate donations for Notre-Dame should get a 90% tax deduction (rather than the standard 60%) was retracted after public outcry.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Alderman |first1=Liz |last2=Erlanger |first2=Steven |title=As Rich Lavish Cash on Notre-Dame, Many Ask: What About the Needy? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/17/world/europe/yellow-vest-notre-dame-fire-donations.html |work=The New York Times |date=17 April 2019 |accessdate=20 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420191224/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/17/world/europe/yellow-vest-notre-dame-fire-donations.html |archive-date=20 April 2019 |url-status=live |url-access=limited}}</ref> Some donors have said they will not seek tax deductions.<ref name=\"anger\" /> Those who do not pay income tax (more than half of French taxpayers, including many working- and middle-class donors) are not eligible for tax deductions.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reich |first1=Rob |title=Donors have pledged nearly a billion euros to restore Notre Dame. You may not want to thank them. |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2019/04/19/donors-have-pledged-nearly-billion-euros-restore-notre-dame-you-may-not-want-thank-them/ |work=The Washington Post |date=19 April 2019 |accessdate=18 May 2019 |url-access=limited}}</ref>\n\nAs of 14 June, only \u20ac80{{nbsp}}million had been collected.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://g1.globo.com/mundo/noticia/2019/06/14/apenas-9percent-das-promessas-de-doacoes-a-notre-dame-foram-cumpridas.ghtml |date=14 June 2019 |title=Only 9% of the donation pledges to Notre-Dame have been fulfilled |work=[[G1 (website)|Global G1]] |accessdate=14 June 2019 |language=pt}}</ref><ref name=\"France24\">{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190614-only-9-millions-pledged-notre-dame-handed-over |date=14 June 2019 |title=Only 9% of millions pledged for Notre-Dame handed over |work=[[France 24]] |accessdate=14 June 2019 |agency=AFP}}</ref> The minister in charge of national museums and monuments, [[Franck Riester]], predicted that further donations would materialise as reconstruction work progressed,<ref name=\"France24\"/> though it was reported that some who made pledges have renounced them because fundraising has been so successful.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.france24.com/en/20190615-paris-notre-dame-cathedral-first-mass-after-devastating-fire-france |date=15 June 2019 |title=Paris's Notre-Dame Cathedral to hold first mass since devastating fire |work=[[France 24]] |accessdate=15 June 2019 |agency=AFP}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[York Minster#1984 fire|1984 York Minster fire]]\n* [[List of building or structure fires]]\n* [[List of destroyed heritage]]\n* [[List of fires at major places of worship]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|2019 Notre-Dame de Paris fire}}\n* {{Official website|http://www.notredamedeparis.fr/en|Notre-Dame de Paris}} \u2013 official site\n* [https://www.nga.gov/research/library/imagecollections/features/notre-dame.html Before the Fire: Notre-Dame de Paris in Pictures]\n\n{{Notre-Dame de Paris|state=collapsed}}\n{{Portal bar|Architecture|Catholicism|France}}\n\n[[Category:4th arrondissement of Paris]]\n[[Category:2019 fires in Europe]]\n[[Category:2019 in Christianity]]\n[[Category:2019 in Paris]]\n[[Category:April 2019 events in France]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n[[Category:Building and structure fires in France]]\n[[Category:Building collapses in 2019]]\n[[Category:Fires in Paris]]\n[[Category:Notre-Dame de Paris]]\n[[Category:Paris Fire Brigade]]\n[[Category:Religious buildings and structures fires]]\n", "name_user": "Ericoides", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDamage:no -ly hyphen", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Notre-Dame_de_Paris_fire"}
{"title_page": "Counter admiral", "text_new": "{{Navalranks}}\n'''Counter admiral''' is a [[military rank|rank]] found in many navies of the world, but no longer used in [[English-speaking countries]], where the equivalent rank is [[rear admiral]]. The term derives from the French ''contre-amiral''.<ref name=oxford>Oxford English Dictionary. counter-admiral, n.\nSecond edition, 1989; online version June 2011. <http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/42655>; accessed 22 June 2011.</ref>\n\nIn modern navies that use it, rear (counter) admiral is generally, although not always, the lowest [[flag officer]] rank (in the [[German Navy]], for instance, ''[[Flottillenadmiral]]'' ranks below ''Konteradmiral''; in the [[Royal Canadian Navy]], ''contre-amiral''/rear admiral ranks above ''[[Commodore (rank)|commodore]]''). As one of the accouterments of their rank, Counter admirals are issued counters to stand behind, as opposed to desks that are issued to higher ranking flag officers.\n\n==Portugal and Brazil==\n<gallery>\nPOR-Navy-OF7.svg|Sleeve insignia (Portuguese Navy)\nContra-Almirante_MB.png|Shoulder insignia (Brazilian Navy)\n</gallery>\nIn the [[Portuguese Navy|navies of Portugal]] and [[Brazilian Navy|Brazil]], the rank of ''contra-almirante'' is the lowest of the permanent flag officer ranks. In the Portuguese Navy there is a flag officer rank below that of ''contra-almirante'', the rank of ''comodoro'' ([[commodore (rank)|commodore]]), but this is only a provisional appointment, assigned to some [[captain (navy)|captains]].\n\nUntil the end of the 19th century, the present rank of ''contra-almirante'' was named ''chefe de esquadra'' (chief of squadron), both in the Portuguese and the Brazilian navies.\n\n==France==\n<gallery>French_Navy-Rama_NG-OF6.svg|Shoulder insignia\n</gallery>\n\n''Contre-Amiral'' is the [[OF-6]] rank of the ''[[Marine nationale]]''.\n\n==Germany==\n[[File:Naval Ensign of Germany.svg|left|30px]] '''[[Konteradmiral]]''' is an [[OF-7]] [[two-star rank]] of [[Deutsche Marine]] (German Navy), equivalent to the [[Generalmajor]] (en: [[Major general]]) in the [[German Army]] and the [[German Air Force]].\n\nSee also:\n{{Main article|Konteradmiral|List of German admirals}}\n\n==Former USSR and Russia==\n<gallery>\nRAF_N_F6RearAdm_since_2010par.svg|Shoulder insignia (Soviet Navy)\nRussia-Navy-OF-6-2010.svg|Shoulder insignia (Russian Navy)\nRAF N F6-KontAdm sleeve.png|Sleeve insignia (Russian Navy)\n</gallery>\n\n''Kontr-admiral'' was the lowest flag officer rank of the [[Soviet Navy]] and is the lowest flag rank of the [[Russian Navy]], similar to an OF-6 officer.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{| class=\"toccolours\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0.5em auto; clear: both;\"\n|-\n|width=\"30%\" align=\"center\"|Junior Rank<br>'''[[Flottillenadmiral]]'''\n|width=\"40%\" align=\"center\"|'''[[File:Bundeswehr Logo Marine with lettering.svg|50px]]<br />'''[[Rank insignia of the German Bundeswehr#Commissioned officers (CO/ de: Offiziere)|German Navy officer rank]]'''<br>'''Konteradmiral'''\n|width=\"30%\" align=\"center\"|Senior Rank<br>'''[[Vizeadmiral]]'''\n|}\n{{Polish officer ranks}}\n\n[[Category:Admirals]]\n[[Category:Naval ranks]]\n\n\n{{mil-rank-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Navalranks}}\n'''Counter admiral''' is a [[military rank|rank]] found in many navies of the world, but no longer used in [[English-speaking countries]], where the equivalent rank is [[rear admiral]]. The term derives from the French ''contre-amiral''.<ref name=oxford>Oxford English Dictionary. counter-admiral, n.\nSecond edition, 1989; online version June 2011. <http://www.oed.com/view/Entry/42655>; accessed 22 June 2011.</ref>\n\nIn modern navies that use it, rear (counter) admiral is generally, although not always, the lowest [[flag officer]] rank (in the [[German Navy]], for instance, ''[[Flottillenadmiral]]'' ranks below ''Konteradmiral''; in the [[Royal Canadian Navy]], ''contre-amiral''/rear admiral ranks above ''[[Commodore (rank)|commodore]]'').\n\n==Portugal and Brazil==\n<gallery>\nPOR-Navy-OF7.svg|Sleeve insignia (Portuguese Navy)\nContra-Almirante_MB.png|Shoulder insignia (Brazilian Navy)\n</gallery>\nIn the [[Portuguese Navy|navies of Portugal]] and [[Brazilian Navy|Brazil]], the rank of ''contra-almirante'' is the lowest of the permanent flag officer ranks. In the Portuguese Navy there is a flag officer rank below that of ''contra-almirante'', the rank of ''comodoro'' ([[commodore (rank)|commodore]]), but this is only a provisional appointment, assigned to some [[captain (navy)|captains]].\n\nUntil the end of the 19th century, the present rank of ''contra-almirante'' was named ''chefe de esquadra'' (chief of squadron), both in the Portuguese and the Brazilian navies.\n\n==France==\n<gallery>French_Navy-Rama_NG-OF6.svg|Shoulder insignia\n</gallery>\n\n''Contre-Amiral'' is the [[OF-6]] rank of the ''[[Marine nationale]]''.\n\n==Germany==\n[[File:Naval Ensign of Germany.svg|left|30px]] '''[[Konteradmiral]]''' is an [[OF-7]] [[two-star rank]] of [[Deutsche Marine]] (German Navy), equivalent to the [[Generalmajor]] (en: [[Major general]]) in the [[German Army]] and the [[German Air Force]].\n\nSee also:\n{{Main article|Konteradmiral|List of German admirals}}\n\n==Former USSR and Russia==\n<gallery>\nRAF_N_F6RearAdm_since_2010par.svg|Shoulder insignia (Soviet Navy)\nRussia-Navy-OF-6-2010.svg|Shoulder insignia (Russian Navy)\nRAF N F6-KontAdm sleeve.png|Sleeve insignia (Russian Navy)\n</gallery>\n\n''Kontr-admiral'' was the lowest flag officer rank of the [[Soviet Navy]] and is the lowest flag rank of the [[Russian Navy]], similar to an OF-6 officer.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{| class=\"toccolours\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; margin: 0.5em auto; clear: both;\"\n|-\n|width=\"30%\" align=\"center\"|Junior Rank<br>'''[[Flottillenadmiral]]'''\n|width=\"40%\" align=\"center\"|'''[[File:Bundeswehr Logo Marine with lettering.svg|50px]]<br />'''[[Rank insignia of the German Bundeswehr#Commissioned officers (CO/ de: Offiziere)|German Navy officer rank]]'''<br>'''Konteradmiral'''\n|width=\"30%\" align=\"center\"|Senior Rank<br>'''[[Vizeadmiral]]'''\n|}\n{{Polish officer ranks}}\n\n[[Category:Admirals]]\n[[Category:Naval ranks]]\n\n\n{{mil-rank-stub}}\n", "name_user": "2600:1000:b129:9677:b920:aa64:bf98:db57", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(added content)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Counter_admiral"}
